ider carries passengers in Maragua town, Murang'a County on December 25, 2020 as people travelled upcountry for Christmas. Nairobi-based businessman Amos Ngumbi distributes foodstuffs to his neighbors in Kikunduku village, Makueni County on December 24, 2020. Children ride on a merry-go-round at Uhuru Park during Christmas on December 25, 2020. Hundreds  flock Nyali beach in Mombasa to celebrate Christmas on December 25, 2020. The bridge will be officially opened on January 1, 2021. The coronavirus pandemic has disrupted the very essence of Christian celebrations this festive season.